{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775892594726,"sessionID":"ses_2848da925ffeSsivYQEgeFrCaj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b7280240019cmJ9QGtyE5YhM","messageID":"msg_d7b72757b001IKBzJzZuOh6agq","sessionID":"ses_2848da925ffeSsivYQEgeFrCaj","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892599397,"sessionID":"ses_2848da925ffeSsivYQEgeFrCaj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b72826e001nST0Eq0w8dkSoS","messageID":"msg_d7b72757b001IKBzJzZuOh6agq","sessionID":"ses_2848da925ffeSsivYQEgeFrCaj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_69478d69cb8644829c5a613b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-005 Sandbox Creation Processor\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation for the Sandbox processor module within `pkg/workloadmanager`. The processor handles creation and lifecycle management of sandbox environments using Kubernetes custom resources.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Component Structure\n10: \n11: ```\n12: pkg/workloadmanager/\n13: ├── processor/\n14: │   ├── sandbox_processor.go      # Main processor implementation\n15: │   ├── sandbox_processor_test.go # Unit tests\n16: │   └── interface.go              # Processor interface definition\n17: ├── types/\n18: │   └── sandbox.go                # Sandbox data structures\n19: └── config/\n20:     └── sandbox_config.go         # Configuration structures\n21: ```\n22: \n23: ### Integration Points\n24: \n25: - **Client-go**: Uses generated typed client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n26: - **Informers**: Watches `CodeInterpreter` and `AgentRuntime` resources\n27: - **Listers**: Provides cached read access to resources\n28: \n29: ## Data Structures\n30: \n31: ### Sandbox Processor\n32: \n33: ```go\n34: type SandboxProcessor struct {\n35:     client       runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n36:     informer     cache.SharedIndexInformer\n37:     lister       runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister\n38:     config       *SandboxConfig\n39:     eventHandler cache.ResourceEventHandlerRegistration\n40: }\n41: \n42: type SandboxConfig struct {\n43:     DefaultNamespace     string\n44:     ResourceTimeout      time.Duration\n45:     DefaultCPURequest    string\n46:     DefaultMemoryRequest string\n47:     AllowedRuntimes      []string\n48: }\n49: ```\n50: \n51: ### Sandbox Context\n52: \n53: ```go\n54: type SandboxContext struct {\n55:     Name         string\n56:     Namespace    string\n57:     RuntimeType  string\n58:     Owner        string\n59:     Labels       map[string]string\n60:     Annotations  map[string]string\n61:     Resources    v1.ResourceRequirements\n62: }\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ## API Contracts\n66: \n67: ### Processor Interface\n68: \n69: ```go\n70: type Processor interface {\n71:     Create(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxContext) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n72:     Update(ctx context.Context, sandbox *SandboxContext) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n73:     Delete(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) error\n74:     Get(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n75:     Watch(ctx context.Context, namespace string) (watch.Interface, error)\n76: }\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### Create Operation\n80: \n81: **Input**: `SandboxContext` with required fields: `Name`, `Namespace`, `RuntimeType`\n82: \n83: **Output**: `*CodeInterpreter` or error\n84: \n85: **Behavior**:\n86: 1. Validate sandbox context (required fields, allowed runtime types)\n87: 2. Check for existing sandbox with same name\n88: 3. Construct `CodeInterpreter` object with proper labels/annotations\n89: 4. Apply resource quotas from config\n90: 5. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Create()`\n91: 6. Return created resource or error\n92: \n93: ### Update Operation\n94: \n95: **Input**: `SandboxContext` with `Name`, `Namespace`, and fields to update\n96: \n97: **Output**: `*CodeInterpreter` or error\n98: \n99: **Behavior**:\n100: 1. Fetch existing `CodeInterpreter`\n101: 2. Apply updates (resources, labels, annotations)\n102: 3. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Update()`\n103: 4. Return updated resource\n104: \n105: ### Delete Operation\n106: \n107: **Input**: `name`, `namespace`\n108: \n109: **Output**: error\n110: \n111: **Behavior**:\n112: 1. Call `client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete()`\n113: 2. Handle `NotFound` errors gracefully\n114: \n115: ## Error Handling\n116: \n117: ### Error Types\n118: \n119: ```go\n120: var (\n121:     ErrSandboxNotFound     = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")\n122:     ErrSandboxExists       = errors.New(\"sandbox already exists\")\n123:     ErrInvalidRuntime      = errors.New(\"invalid runtime type\")\n124:     ErrValidationFailed    = errors.New(\"sandbox validation failed\")\n125:     ErrCreateTimeout       = errors.New(\"sandbox creation timeout\")\n126: )\n127: ```\n128: \n129: ### Error Wrapping\n130: \n131: All errors wrapped with context using `fmt.Errorf(\"context: %w\", err)`.\n132: \n133: ### Retry Strategy\n134: \n135: - Transient errors: 3 retries with exponential backoff (100ms, 200ms, 400ms)\n136: - `TooManyRequests`: Respect `Retry-After` header\n137: - Permanent errors: Return immediately without retry\n138: \n139: ## Testing Strategy\n140: \n141: ### Unit Tests\n142: \n143: **File**: `processor/sandbox_processor_test.go`\n144: \n145: **Test Cases**:\n146: 1. `TestCreateSandbox_Success` - Valid sandbox creation\n147: 2. `TestCreateSandbox_InvalidRuntime` - Rejected runtime type\n148: 3. `TestCreateSandbox_AlreadyExists` - Duplicate creation\n149: 4. `TestUpdateSandbox_Success` - Resource update\n150: 5. `TestDeleteSandbox_Success` - Normal deletion\n151: 6. `TestDeleteSandbox_NotFound` - Idempotent delete\n152: 7. `TestGetSandbox_Success` - Retrieve existing sandbox\n153: \n154: ### Test Fixtures\n155: \n156: ```go\n157: func newTestSandboxContext(name, runtime string) *SandboxContext {\n158:     return &SandboxContext{\n159:         Name:        name,\n160:         Namespace:   \"default\",\n161:         RuntimeType: runtime,\n162:         Resources: v1.ResourceRequirements{\n163:             Requests: v1.ResourceList{\n164:                 v1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(\"100m\"),\n165:                 v1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(\"128Mi\"),\n166:             },\n167:         },\n168:     }\n169: }\n170: ```\n171: \n172: ### Mock Setup\n173: \n174: ```go\n175: func newTestProcessor(client runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface) *SandboxProcessor {\n176:     return &SandboxProcessor{\n177:         client: client,\n178:         config: &SandboxConfig{\n179:             DefaultNamespace: \"default\",\n180:             ResourceTimeout:  30 * time.Second,\n181:             AllowedRuntimes:  []string{\"python\", \"nodejs\", \"go\"},\n182:         },\n183:     }\n184: }\n185: ```\n186: \n187: ### Integration Tests\n188: \n189: **File**: `processor/sandbox_processor_integration_test.go`\n190: \n191: Tests against real Kubernetes cluster (kind) using `envtest`:\n192: 1. Full lifecycle (create → update → delete)\n193: 2. Concurrent operations\n194: 3. Resource quota enforcement\n195: \n196: ## Implementation Notes\n197: \n198: ### Resource Naming\n199: \n200: CodeInterpreter resources follow pattern: `sandbox-{owner}-{uuid}`\n201: \n202: ### Labels\n203: \n204: Standard labels applied to all sandboxes:\n205: - `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube`\n206: - `app.kubernetes.io/component: sandbox`\n207: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/owner: <owner>`\n208: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/runtime: <runtime-type>`\n209: \n210: ### Annotations\n211: \n212: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/created-at: <RFC3339>`\n213: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/last-updated: <RFC3339>`\n214: \n215: ### Timeout Handling\n216: \n217: Creation uses context with timeout from `config.ResourceTimeout`. Watch for resource to reach `Ready` phase within timeout window.\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: # Design: AR-014 Valkey Storage Implementation\n222: \n223: ## Overview\n224: \n225: This document describes the technical implementation of the session store for AgentCube, supporting both Redis and Valkey backends. The store persists sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking to enable garbage collection.\n226: \n227: ## Architecture\n228: \n229: ```\n230: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n231: │                     Application Layer                        │\n232: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n233:                             │\n234:                             ▼\n235: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n236: │                    store.Singleton                           │\n237: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n238: │  │ Storage() → Store (sync.Once initialization)         │   │\n239: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n240: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n241:                             │\n242:             ┌───────────────┴───────────────┐\n243:             │ STORE_TYPE (case-insensitive) │\n244:             ▼                               ▼\n245: ┌───────────────────────┐       ┌───────────────────────┐\n246: │    redisStore         │       │    valkeyStore        │\n247: │  - *redisv9.Client    │       │  - valkey.Client      │\n248: │  - sessionPrefix      │       │  - sessionPrefix      │\n249: │  - expiryIndexKey     │       │  - expiryIndexKey     │\n250: │  - lastActivityIndex  │       │  - lastActivityIndex  │\n251: └───────────────────────┘       └───────────────────────┘\n252:             │                               │\n253:             ▼                               ▼\n254: ┌───────────────────────┐       ┌───────────────────────┐\n255: │   Redis Server        │       │   Valkey Server       │\n256: │   - session:{id}      │       │   - session:{id}      │\n257: │   - session:expiry    │       │   - session:expiry    │\n258: │   - session:last_activity│    │   - session:last_activity│\n259: └───────────────────────┘       └───────────────────────┘\n260: ```\n261: \n262: ## Data Structures\n263: \n264: ### SandboxInfo (Primary Document)\n265: \n266: **Package:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n267: \n268: ```go\n269: type SandboxInfo struct {\n270:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n271:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n272:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n273:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n274:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n275:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n276:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n277:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n278:     Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n279: }\n280: \n281: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n282:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n283:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n284:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n285: }\n286: ```\n287: \n288: **Storage Format:** JSON-serialized string stored at key `session:{sessionID}`\n289: \n290: ### Index Structures\n291: \n292: | Index | Type | Key | Member | Score |\n293: |-------|------|-----|--------|-------|\n294: | Expiry | Sorted Set | `session:expiry` | sessionID | `ExpiresAt.Unix()` |\n295: | Last Activity | Sorted Set | `session:last_activity` | sessionID | `lastActivity.Unix()` |\n296: \n297: ## Store Interface Contract\n298: \n299: **Package:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n300: \n301: ```go\n302: type Store interface {\n303:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n304:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n305:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n306:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n307:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n308:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n309:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n310:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n311:     Close() error\n312: }\n313: ```\n314: \n315: ### Error Handling\n316: \n317: ```go\n318: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n319: ```\n320: \n321: | Error Condition | Error Value |\n322: |-----------------|-------------|\n323: | Key does not exist on GET | `ErrNotFound` |\n324: | Session missing on UpdateSessionLastActivity | `ErrNotFound` |\n325: | SET XX fails on UpdateSandbox (key not exists) | `key not exists` error |\n326: | Nil sandbox on StoreSandbox | validation error |\n327: | Zero ExpiresAt on StoreSandbox | validation error |\n328: \n329: ## Implementation Details\n330: \n331: ### Singleton Pattern (singleton.go)\n332: \n333: ```go\n334: var (\n335:     initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n336:     provider      Store\n337: )\n338: \n339: func Storage() Store {\n340:     initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)\n341:     return provider\n342: }\n343: \n344: func initStore() error {\n345:     storeType := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"STORE_TYPE\"))\n346:     if storeType == \"\" {\n347:         storeType = redisStoreType\n348:     }\n349:     \n350:     switch storeType {\n351:     case redisStoreType:\n352:         provider = newRedisStore()\n353:     case valkeyStoreType:\n354:         provider = newValkeyStore()\n355:     default:\n356:         return fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported store type: %s\", storeType)\n357:     }\n358:     return nil\n359: }\n360: ```\n361: \n362: ### Redis Implementation (store_redis.go)\n363: \n364: #### Connection Options\n365: \n366: ```go\n367: func makeRedisOptions() (*redisv9.Options, error) {\n368:     redisAddr := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_ADDR\")\n369:     if redisAddr == \"\" {\n370:         return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")\n371:     }\n372:     \n373:     redisPassword := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD\")\n374:     passwordRequired := true\n375:     if v := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"); strings.ToLower(v) == \"false\" {\n376:         passwordRequired = false\n377:     }\n378:     \n379:     if passwordRequired && redisPassword == \"\" {\n380:         return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required\")\n381:     }\n382:     \n383:     return &redisv9.Options{\n384:         Addr:     redisAddr,\n385:         Password: redisPassword,\n386:     }, nil\n387: }\n388: ```\n389: \n390: #### Key Operations\n391: \n392: | Operation | Redis Commands | Notes |\n393: |-----------|----------------|-------|\n394: | Ping | `PING` → expect \"PONG\" | Health check |\n395: | GetSandboxBySessionID | `GET session:{id}` | Return `ErrNotFound` on Nil |\n396: | StoreSandbox | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD expiry`, `ZADD last_activity` | Atomic batch |\n397: | UpdateSandbox | `SET key value XX` | Only update value, not indexes |\n398: | DeleteSandboxBySessionID | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` | Full cleanup |\n399: | ListExpiredSandboxes | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` + pipeline GETs | Skip missing keys |\n400: | ListInactiveSandboxes | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` + pipeline GETs | Skip missing keys |\n401: | UpdateSessionLastActivity | `EXISTS key` → `ZADD last_activity` | Verify key exists first |\n402: \n403: ### Valkey Implementation (store_valkey.go)\n404: \n405: #### Connection Options\n406: \n407: ```go\n408: func makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error) {\n409:     valkeyAddr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n410:     if valkeyAddr == \"\" {\n411:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n412:     }\n413:     \n414:     valkeyPassword := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n415:     passwordRequired := true\n416:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"); strings.ToLower(v) == \"false\" {\n417:         passwordRequired = false\n418:     }\n419:     \n420:     if passwordRequired && valkeyPassword == \"\" {\n421:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required\")\n422:     }\n423:     \n424:     opt := &valkey.ClientOption{\n425:         InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n426:         Password:    valkeyPassword,\n427:     }\n428:     \n429:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\"); v != \"\" {\n430:         if disable, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && disable {\n431:             opt.DisableCache = true\n432:         }\n433:     }\n434:     \n435:     if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\"); v != \"\" {\n436:         if force, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && force {\n437:             opt.ForceSingleClient = true\n438:         }\n439:     }\n440:     \n441:     if opt.DisableCache || opt.ForceSingleClient {\n442:         klog.V(4).Infof(\"Valkey options: DisableCache=%v, ForceSingleClient=%v\", \n443:             opt.DisableCache, opt.ForceSingleClient)\n444:     }\n445:     \n446:     return opt, nil\n447: }\n448: ```\n449: \n450: #### Key Operations\n451: \n452: | Operation | Valkey API | Notes |\n453: |-----------|------------|-------|\n454: | Ping | `B().Ping()` → string \"PONG\" | Health check |\n455: | GetSandboxBySessionID | `B().Get().Key(key)` | `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n456: | StoreSandbox | `DoMulti`: SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity | Atomic batch |\n457: | UpdateSandbox | `SET ... XX` | Response must be \"OK\" |\n458: | DeleteSandboxBySessionID | `DoMulti`: DEL, ZREM expiry, ZREM last_activity | Full cleanup |\n459: | ListExpiredSandboxes | `Zrangebyscore` with Min(\"-inf\"), Max(before.Unix), Limit(0, limit) | Use MGET for batch load |\n460: | ListInactiveSandboxes | Same on last_activity key | MGET requires same slot |\n461: | UpdateSessionLastActivity | `Exists` → int64 must be 1, then `Zadd` | Verify existence first |\n462: \n463: #### MGET Optimization Note\n464: \n465: The `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` function uses single `MGET` for batch loading. This assumes all `session:{id}` keys are in the same cluster slot, which should be ensured through deployment configuration (e.g., hash tags or single-node deployment).\n466: \n467: ## Environment Configuration\n468: \n469: ### Common Variables\n470: \n471: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n472: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n473: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Provider selection (`redis` or `valkey`), case-insensitive |\n474: \n475: ### Redis-Specific Variables\n476: \n477: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n478: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n479: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis server address (host:port) |\n480: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes* | - | Password for authentication |\n481: | `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n482: \n483: \\* Required unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` (case-insensitive)\n484: \n485: ### Valkey-Specific Variables\n486: \n487: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n488: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n489: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated list of Valkey addresses |\n490: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes* | - | Password for authentication |\n491: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n492: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to disable client-side caching |\n493: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to force single-client mode |\n494: \n495: ## API Contracts\n496: \n497: ### StoreSandbox Validation\n498: \n499: ```go\n500: func (s *redisStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxInfo *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n501:     if sandboxInfo == nil {\n502:         return errors.New(\"sandbox cannot be nil\")\n503:     }\n504:     if sandboxInfo.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n505:         return errors.New(\"expiresAt cannot be zero\")\n506:     }\n507:     // ... proceed with atomic pipeline\n508: }\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ### UpdateSandbox Semantics\n512: \n513: - **Only updates the JSON value** using `SET key value XX`\n514: - **Does NOT modify** expiry or last-activity sorted set entries\n515: - **Fails if key does not exist** (Redis: returns false; Valkey: response != \"OK\")\n516: \n517: ### List Operations - Orphan Handling\n518: \n519: Both `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` tolerate orphan ZSET entries (session IDs in the index without corresponding JSON documents):\n520: \n521: ```go\n522: // Skip entries where GET returns nil/empty\n523: if result == nil || result == \"\" {\n524:     continue // orphan ZSET member, skip\n525: }\n526: ```\n527: \n528: ### UpdateSessionLastActivity Preconditions\n529: \n530: 1. Session ID must be non-empty\n531: 2. If `at` is zero time, use `time.Now()`\n532: 3. **Verify session key exists** before ZADD\n533: 4. Return `ErrNotFound` if key does not exist\n534: \n535: ## Testing Strategy\n536: \n537: ### Unit Tests\n538: \n539: **File:** `pkg/store/store_redis_test.go`, `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go`\n540: \n541: | Test Case | Description |\n542: |-----------|-------------|\n543: | `TestPing_Success` | Verify PING returns PONG |\n544: | `TestGetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound` | Verify `ErrNotFound` on missing key |\n545: | `TestStoreSandbox_NilRejected` | Verify nil sandbox validation |\n546: | `TestStoreSandbox_ZeroExpiresAtRejected` | Verify zero time validation |\n547: | `TestStoreSandbox_Atomicity` | Verify all three commands execute or fail together |\n548: | `TestUpdateSandbox_MissingKey` | Verify error when key doesn't exist |\n549: | `TestDeleteSandboxBySessionID_FullCleanup` | Verify DEL + ZREM operations |\n550: | `TestListExpiredSandboxes_OrphanTolerance` | Verify missing keys are skipped |\n551: | `TestUpdateSessionLastActivity_MissingSession` | Verify `ErrNotFound` on missing key |\n552: | `TestStorage_Singleton` | Verify sync.Once behavior with concurrent calls |\n553: \n554: ### Integration Tests\n555: \n556: **File:** `pkg/store/integration_test.go`\n557: \n558: | Test Case | Backend | Description |\n559: |-----------|---------|-------------|\n560: | `TestIntegration_StoreAndGet` | Redis, Valkey | Full store → get cycle |\n561: | `TestIntegration_ExpiryIndex` | Redis, Valkey | Verify ZSET score is correct |\n562: | `TestIntegration_LastActivityIndex` | Redis, Valkey | Verify activity tracking |\n563: | `TestIntegration_GC_ListExpired` | Redis, Valkey | Garbage collection query |\n564: | `TestIntegration_GC_ListInactive` | Redis, Valkey | Inactivity detection |\n565: | `TestIntegration_ConcurrentAccess` | Redis, Valkey | Concurrent store/update operations |\n566: \n567: ### Test Fixtures\n568: \n569: ```go\n570: func newTestSandbox(sessionID string, expiresAt time.Time) *types.SandboxInfo {\n571:     return &types.SandboxInfo{\n572:         Kind:             \"sandbox\",\n573:         SandboxID:        \"sandbox-123\",\n574:         SandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n575:         Name:             \"test-sandbox\",\n576:         SessionID:        sessionID,\n577:         CreatedAt:        time.Now(),\n578:         ExpiresAt:        expiresAt,\n579:         Status:           \"running\",\n580:         EntryPoints:      []types.SandboxEntryPoint{},\n581:     }\n582: }\n583: ```\n584: \n585: ## Dependencies\n586: \n587: ```go\n588: import (\n589:     // Redis client\n590:     \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n591:     \n592:     // Valkey client\n593:     \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n594:     \n595:     // Logging\n596:     \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n597:     \n598:     // Internal types\n599:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n600: )\n601: ```\n602: \n603: ## File Structure\n604: \n605: ```\n606: pkg/store/\n607: ├── store.go                    # Store interface definition\n608: ├── singleton.go                # Storage() singleton with sync.Once\n609: ├── store_redis.go              # Redis implementation\n610: ├── store_redis_test.go         # Redis unit tests\n611: ├── store_valkey.go             # Valkey implementation\n612: ├── store_valkey_test.go        # Valkey unit tests\n613: ├── integration_test.go         # Integration tests (both backends)\n614: └── errors.go                   # ErrNotFound and other package errors\n615: ```\n616: \n617: ## Regeneration\n618: \n619: Client code regeneration (if Kubernetes client updates are needed):\n620: \n621: ```bash\n622: make gen-client  # Runs hack/update-codegen.sh\n623: ```\n624: \n625: Uses `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with `--with-watch` flag.\n626: \n627: ---\n628: \n629: # Design: AR-017 PicoD JWT Middleware\n630: \n631: ## Overview\n632: \n633: This document describes the technical implementation of JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD HTTP server. The middleware validates JWT tokens on incoming requests and injects validated claims into the request context for downstream handlers.\n634: \n635: ## Architecture\n636: \n637: ### Component Placement\n638: \n639: ```\n640: ┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐\n641: │   Client    │────▶│  PicoD HTTP  │────▶│ JWT Middle- │────▶│   Handler   │\n642: │  (with JWT) │     │   Server     │     │   ware      │     │  (Business) │\n643: └─────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘\n644: ```\n645: \n646: ### Package Structure\n647: \n648: ```\n649: pkg/picod/\n650: ├── jwt/\n651: │   ├── middleware.go      # HTTP middleware handler\n652: │   ├── validator.go       # JWT validation logic\n653: │   ├── claims.go          # Custom claims structure\n654: │   ├── config.go          # Configuration types\n655: │   └── error.go           # Error types\n656: ├── server.go              # PicoD server integration\n657: └── ...\n658: ```\n659: \n660: ### Dependencies\n661: \n662: - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` - JWT parsing and validation\n663: - Standard library: `net/http`, `context`, `errors`, `fmt`, `strings`\n664: \n665: ## Data Structures\n666: \n667: ### Config\n668: \n669: ```go\n670: type Config struct {\n671:     // SigningKey is the secret key for HMAC verification\n672:     SigningKey []byte\n673:     \n674:     // SigningMethod is the signing algorithm (default: \"HS256\")\n675:     SigningMethod string\n676:     \n677:     // SkipPaths are paths that bypass JWT validation\n678:     SkipPaths map[string]bool\n679:     \n680:     // TokenLookup defines where to extract token from\n681:     // Format: \"header:<name>\" or \"query:<name>\"\n682:     TokenLookup string\n683:     \n684:     // ContextKey is the key to store claims in context\n685:     ContextKey string\n686:     \n687:     // ExpiryMax is the maximum allowed token expiry duration\n688:     ExpiryMax time.Duration\n689: }\n690: ```\n691: \n692: ### Claims\n693: \n694: ```go\n695: type Claims struct {\n696:     jwt.RegisteredClaims\n697:     \n698:     // Custom claims\n699:     UserID    string   `json:\"user_id,omitempty\"`\n700:     Namespace string   `json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n701:     Roles     []string `json:\"roles,omitempty\"`\n702: }\n703: ```\n704: \n705: ### Middleware\n706: \n707: ```go\n708: type Middleware struct {\n709:     config  *Config\n710:     keyFunc jwt.Keyfunc\n711:     parser  *jwt.Parser\n712: }\n713: ```\n714: \n715: ### Context Keys\n716: \n717: ```go\n718: type contextKey string\n719: \n720: const (\n721:     ClaimsKey contextKey = \"jwt_claims\"\n722: )\n723: ```\n724: \n725: ## API Contracts\n726: \n727: ### Middleware Constructor\n728: \n729: ```go\n730: func New(config Config) (*Middleware, error)\n731: ```\n732: \n733: **Behavior**:\n734: 1. Validate config (SigningKey required, valid SigningMethod)\n735: 2. Set defaults (SigningMethod=\"HS256\", TokenLookup=\"header:Authorization\")\n736: 3. Create keyFunc for HMAC verification\n737: 4. Configure parser with allowed methods\n738: 5. Return middleware instance or error\n739: \n740: ### HTTP Handler\n741: \n742: ```go\n743: func (m *Middleware) Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n744: ```\n745: \n746: **Behavior**:\n747: 1. Check if request path is in SkipPaths\n748: 2. Extract token from header/query per TokenLookup\n749: 3. Parse and validate JWT\n750: 4. On success: inject claims to context, call next handler\n751: 5. On failure: return 401/403 with JSON error response\n752: \n753: ### Context Extraction\n754: \n755: ```go\n756: func GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)\n757: ```\n758: \n759: **Behavior**:\n760: 1. Extract claims from context using ClaimsKey\n761: 2. Return claims and true if present, nil and false otherwise\n762: \n763: ### Error Response Format\n764: \n765: ```go\n766: type Error struct {\n767:     Code    string `json:\"code\"`\n768:     Message string `json:\"message\"`\n769: }\n770: ```\n771: \n772: **Standard Error Codes**:\n773: | Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n774: |------|-------------|-------------|\n775: | `JWT_MISSING` | 401 | No token provided |\n776: | `JWT_INVALID` | 401 | Token format/structure invalid |\n777: | `JWT_EXPIRED` | 401 | Token has expired |\n778: | `JWT_SIGNATURE_INVALID` | 401 | Signature verification failed |\n779: | `JWT_EXPIRY_EXCEEDED` | 401 | Token expiry exceeds maximum allowed |\n780: \n781: ## Implementation Details\n782: \n783: ### Token Extraction\n784: \n785: ```go\n786: func (m *Middleware) extractToken(r *http.Request) (string, error) {\n787:     parts := strings.SplitN(m.config.TokenLookup, \":\", 2)\n788:     if len(parts) != 2 {\n789:         return \"\", errors.New(\"invalid token lookup format\")\n790:     }\n791:     \n792:     switch parts[0] {\n793:     case \"header\":\n794:         auth := r.Header.Get(parts[1])\n795:         if auth == \"\" {\n796:             return \"\", ErrTokenMissing\n797:         }\n798:         // Strip \"Bearer \" prefix if present\n799:         return strings.TrimPrefix(auth, \"Bearer \"), nil\n800:         \n801:     case \"query\":\n802:         token := r.URL.Query().Get(parts[1])\n803:         if token == \"\" {\n804:             return \"\", ErrTokenMissing\n805:         }\n806:         return token, nil\n807:         \n808:     default:\n809:         return \"\", errors.New(\"unsupported token lookup type\")\n810:     }\n811: }\n812: ```\n813: \n814: ### Validation Flow\n815: \n816: ```go\n817: func (m *Middleware) validate(tokenString string) (*Claims, error) {\n818:     token, err := m.parser.ParseWithClaims(tokenString, &Claims{}, m.keyFunc)\n819:     if err != nil {\n820:         if errors.Is(err, jwt.ErrTokenExpired) {\n821:             return nil, ErrTokenExpired\n822:         }\n823:         if strings.Contains(err.Error(), \"signature\") {\n824:             return nil, ErrSignatureInvalid\n825:         }\n826:         return nil, ErrTokenInvalid\n827:     }\n828:     \n829:     claims, ok := token.Claims.(*Claims)\n830:     if !ok || !token.Valid {\n831:         return nil, ErrTokenInvalid\n832:     }\n833:     \n834:     // Check max expiry\n835:     if m.config.ExpiryMax > 0 && claims.ExpiresAt != nil {\n836:         if time.Until(claims.ExpiresAt.Time) > m.config.ExpiryMax {\n837:             return nil, ErrExpiryExceeded\n838:         }\n839:     }\n840:     \n841:     return claims, nil\n842: }\n843: ```\n844: \n845: ### HTTP Error Response\n846: \n847: ```go\n848: func writeError(w http.ResponseWriter, statusCode int, code, message string) {\n849:     w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n850:     w.WriteHeader(statusCode)\n851:     json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(Error{Code: code, Message: message})\n852: }\n853: ```\n854: \n855: ## Error Handling\n856: \n857: ### Error Types\n858: \n859: ```go\n860: var (\n861:     ErrTokenMissing     = errors.New(\"jwt: token missing\")\n862:     ErrTokenInvalid     = errors.New(\"jwt: token invalid\")\n863:     ErrTokenExpired     = errors.New(\"jwt: token expired\")\n864:     ErrSignatureInvalid = errors.New(\"jwt: signature invalid\")\n865:     ErrExpiryExceeded   = errors.New(\"jwt: token expiry exceeds maximum\")\n866: )\n867: ```\n868: \n869: ### HTTP Response Codes\n870: \n871: | Scenario | Status | Response Body |\n872: |----------|--------|---------------|\n873: | Missing token | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_MISSING\",\"message\":\"Authorization token required\"}` |\n874: | Invalid format | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_INVALID\",\"message\":\"Invalid token format\"}` |\n875: | Expired token | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_EXPIRED\",\"message\":\"Token has expired\"}` |\n876: | Bad signature | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_SIGNATURE_INVALID\",\"message\":\"Invalid token signature\"}` |\n877: | Expiry exceeded | 401 | `{\"code\":\"JWT_EXPIRY_EXCEEDED\",\"message\":\"Token expiry exceeds maximum allowed\"}` |\n878: \n879: ## Testing Strategy\n880: \n881: ### Unit Tests\n882: \n883: **File**: `jwt/middleware_test.go`\n884: \n885: ```go\n886: // Test middleware construction\n887: - TestNew_ValidConfig\n888: - TestNew_MissingSigningKey\n889: - TestNew_InvalidSigningMethod\n890: \n891: // Test token extraction\n892: - TestExtractToken_Header\n893: - TestExtractToken_Query\n894: - TestExtractToken_BearerPrefix\n895: - TestExtractToken_Missing\n896: \n897: // Test validation\n898: - TestValidateToken_ValidToken\n899: - TestValidateToken_ExpiredToken\n900: - TestValidateToken_InvalidSignature\n901: - TestValidateToken_MalformedToken\n902: - TestValidateToken_ExpiryExceeded\n903: \n904: // Test handler\n905: - TestMiddleware_SkipPath\n906: - TestMiddleware_HeaderExtraction\n907: - TestMiddleware_QueryExtraction\n908: - TestMiddleware_ContextInjection\n909: - TestMiddleware_UnauthorizedResponse\n910: ```\n911: \n912: ### Test Helpers\n913: \n914: **File**: `jwt/test_helpers.go`\n915: \n916: ```go\n917: // GenerateTestToken creates a signed JWT for testing\n918: func GenerateTestToken(claims *Claims, key []byte, expiry time.Duration) (string, error)\n919: \n920: // MockHTTPHandler returns a simple handler for testing\n921: func MockHTTPHandler(statusCode int) http.HandlerFunc\n922: \n923: // NewTestRequest creates an HTTP request with optional JWT\n924: func NewTestRequest(token, path, method string) *http.Request\n925: ```\n926: \n927: ### Integration Tests\n928: \n929: **File**: `jwt/integration_test.go`\n930: \n931: ```go\n932: // Full request flow tests\n933: - TestFullRequestFlow_WithValidJWT\n934: - TestFullRequestFlow_WithExpiredJWT\n935: - TestFullRequestFlow_WithoutJWT\n936: - TestFullRequestFlow_WithSkipPath\n937: - TestFullRequestFlow_CustomClaims\n938: ```\n939: \n940: ### Test Fixtures\n941: \n942: ```go\n943: func newTestConfig() Config {\n944:     return Config{\n945:         SigningKey:  []byte(\"test-secret-key\"),\n946:         SigningMethod: \"HS256\",\n947:         SkipPaths:   map[string]bool{\"/health\": true, \"/public\": true},\n948:         TokenLookup: \"header:Authorization\",\n949:         ContextKey:  \"claims\",\n950:         ExpiryMax:   24 * time.Hour,\n951:     }\n952: }\n953: \n954: func newTestClaims(userID, namespace string, roles []string) *Claims {\n955:     return &Claims{\n956:         RegisteredClaims: jwt.RegisteredClaims{\n957:             ExpiresAt: jwt.NewNumericDate(time.Now().Add(time.Hour)),\n958:             IssuedAt:  jwt.NewNumericDate(time.Now()),\n959:             Subject:   userID,\n960:         },\n961:         UserID:    userID,\n962:         Namespace: namespace,\n963:         Roles:     roles,\n964:     }\n965: }\n966: ```\n967: \n968: ## Security Considerations\n969: \n970: 1. **Key Management**: SigningKey should be loaded from environment variables or secret store, never hardcoded\n971: 2. **Algorithm Restriction**: Explicitly set allowed signing methods in parser to prevent algorithm confusion attacks\n972: 3. **Token Expiry**: Enforce reasonable expiry validation via ExpiryMax (default 24h)\n973: 4. **Path Whitelisting**: Default-deny approach; only paths in SkipPaths are public\n974: 5. **Constant-Time Comparison**: Use hmac.Equal for signature verification (handled by jwt library)\n975: \n976: ## Environment Configuration\n977: \n978: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n979: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n980: | `PICOD_JWT_SIGNING_KEY` | Yes | - | Secret key for HMAC verification |\n981: | `PICOD_JWT_SIGNING_METHOD` | No | `HS256` | Signing algorithm (HS256, HS384, HS512) |\n982: | `PICOD_JWT_SKIP_PATHS` | No | - | Comma-separated list of paths to skip |\n983: | `PICOD_JWT_TOKEN_LOOKUP` | No | `header:Authorization` | Token extraction location |\n984: | `PICOD_JWT_EXPIRY_MAX` | No | `24h` | Maximum allowed token expiry duration |\n985: \n986: ## File Structure\n987: \n988: ```\n989: pkg/picod/jwt/\n990: ├── config.go          # Configuration types and defaults\n991: ├── claims.go          # Claims structure\n992: ├── middleware.go      # HTTP middleware implementation\n993: ├── validator.go       # JWT validation logic\n994: ├── error.go           # Error types and messages\n995: ├── test_helpers.go    # Test utilities\n996: ├── config_test.go     # Configuration tests\n997: ├── middleware_test.go # Middleware unit tests\n998: └── integration_test.go # Integration tests\n999: ```\n1000: \n1001: ---\n1002: \n1003: # Design: AR-035 client-go\n1004: \n1005: ## Overview\n1006: \n1007: Generated Kubernetes client library for API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`. Provides type-safe Go clients, informers, and listers for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources.\n1008: \n1009: ## Architecture\n1010: \n1011: ```\n1012: client-go/\n1013: ├── clientset/              # Typed clientset\n1014: │   ├── versioned/\n1015: │   │   ├── clientset.go           # Clientset, Interface\n1016: │   │   ├── scheme/                # Scheme registration\n1017: │   │   ├── typed/                 # Typed clients per API version\n1018: │   │   │   └── runtime/\n1019: │   │   │       └── v1alpha1/\n1020: │   │   │       ├── runtime_client.go      # RuntimeV1alpha1Client\n1021: │   │   │       ├── agentruntime.go        # AgentRuntimeInterface\n1022: │   │   │       ├── codeinterpreter.go     # CodeInterpreterInterface\n1023: │   │   │       └── fake/                  # Test fakes\n1024: │   │   └── fake/                  # Fake clientset\n1025: │   └── scheme/\n1026: ├── informers/              # SharedInformerFactory\n1027: │   └── externalversions/\n1028: │       ├── factory.go               # SharedInformerFactory\n1029: │       ├── generic.go               # GenericInformer\n1030: │       ├── runtime/                 # Group accessors\n1031: │       │   ├── interface.go\n1032: │       │   └── v1alpha1/\n1033: │       │       ├── interface.go\n1034: │       │       ├── agentruntime.go\n1035: │       │       └── codeinterpreter.go\n1036: │       └── internalinterfaces/      # Shared interfaces\n1037: └── listers/                # Listers (read-only cache)\n1038:     └── runtime/\n1039:         └── v1alpha1/\n1040:             ├── agentruntime.go\n1041:             ├── codeinterpreter.go\n1042:             └── expansion_generated.go\n1043: ```\n1044: \n1045: ## Data Structures\n1046: \n1047: ### Clientset (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n1048: \n1049: ```go\n1050: type Interface interface {\n1051:     Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n1052:     RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n1053: }\n1054: \n1055: type Clientset struct {\n1056:     *discovery.DiscoveryClient\n1057:     runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client\n1058: }\n1059: ```\n1060: \n1061: **Constructors:**\n1062: - `NewForConfig(*rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)` — creates client from kubeconfig\n1063: - `NewForConfigAndClient(*rest.Config, *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)` — with custom HTTP client\n1064: - `NewForConfigOrDie(*rest.Config) *Clientset` — panics on error\n1065: - `New(rest.Interface) *Clientset` — from existing REST interface\n1066: \n1067: ### Typed Client (`clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/`)\n1068: \n1069: ```go\n1070: type RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n1071:     RESTClient() rest.Interface\n1072:     AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n1073:     CodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterInterface\n1074: }\n1075: \n1076: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n1077:     Create(ctx context.Context, obj *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n1078:     Update(ctx context.Context, obj *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n1079:     UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, obj *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n1080:     Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n1081:     DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n1082:     Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n1083:     List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n1084:     Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n1085:     Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n1086: }\n1087: ```\n1088: \n1089: REST configuration:\n1090: - `GroupVersion`: `runtimev1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion`\n1091: - `APIPath`: `/apis`\n1092: - Serializer: from `clientset/versioned/scheme`\n1093: \n1094: ### Informer Factory (`informers/externalversions/factory.go`)\n1095: \n1096: ```go\n1097: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n1098:     Start(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n1099:     Shutdown()\n1100:     WaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n1101:     InformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n1102:     Runtime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n1103: }\n1104: ```\n1105: \n1106: **Options:**\n1107: - `WithCustomResyncConfig(time.Duration)` — per-informer resync period\n1108: - `WithTweakListOptions(TweakListOptionsFunc)` — modify ListOptions\n1109: - `WithNamespace(string)` — filter by namespace\n1110: - `WithTransform(transform.ObjectTransformFunc)` — transform objects before storage\n1111: \n1112: ### Lister (`listers/runtime/v1alpha1/`)\n1113: \n1114: ```go\n1115: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n1116:     List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n1117:     AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n1118: }\n1119: \n1120: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n1121:     List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n1122:     Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n1123: }\n1124: ```\n1125: \n1126: ## API Contracts\n1127: \n1128: ### REST Endpoints\n1129: \n1130: | Resource | HTTP Method | Path | Operation |\n1131: |----------|-------------|------|-----------|\n1132: | `agentruntimes` | POST | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes` | Create |\n1133: | `agentruntimes` | GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Get |\n1134: | `agentruntimes` | PUT | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Update |\n1135: | `agentruntimes` | DELETE | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Delete |\n1136: | `agentruntimes` | GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes` | List |\n1137: | `agentruntimes` | WATCH | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes?watch=true` | Watch |\n1138: | `agentruntimes/status` | PUT | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{ns}/agentruntimes/{name}/status` | UpdateStatus |\n1139: \n1140: ### Error Handling\n1141: \n1142: All client methods return standard Kubernetes API errors:\n1143: \n1144: ```go\n1145: // Common error patterns\n1146: errors.IsNotFound(err)        // 404 Not Found\n1147: errors.IsAlreadyExists(err)   // 409 Conflict\n1148: errors.IsConflict(err)        // 409 Conflict (resource version mismatch)\n1149: errors.IsInvalid(err)         // 422 Unprocessable Entity\n1150: errors.IsTimeout(err)         // 504 Gateway Timeout\n1151: errors.IsServiceUnavailable(err) // 503 Service Unavailable\n1152: ```\n1153: \n1154: **Client construction errors:**\n1155: - Invalid `rest.Config` → `*url.Error`, `*errors.StatusError`\n1156: - Missing credentials → `clientcmd.errConfigurationInvalid`\n1157: \n1158: **Informer errors:**\n1159: - ListWatch failure → propagated via `StopChannel` and error handlers\n1160: - Cache sync timeout → `WaitForCacheSync` returns `false`\n1161: \n1162: ## Testing Strategy\n1163: \n1164: ### Unit Tests\n1165: \n1166: **Location:** `client-go/**/*_test.go`\n1167: \n1168: ```go\n1169: // Example: fake client test\n1170: func TestAgentRuntimeCreate(t *testing.T) {\n1171:     cs := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n1172:     runtime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n1173:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n1174:     }\n1175:     created, err := cs.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(\n1176:         context.TODO(), runtime, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n1177:     if err != nil {\n1178:         t.Fatal(err)\n1179:     }\n1180:     if created.Name != \"test\" {\n1181:         t.Errorf(\"expected name 'test', got %q\", created.Name)\n1182:     }\n1183: }\n1184: ```\n1185: \n1186: ### Integration Tests\n1187: \n1188: **Location:** `test/integration/client-go/`\n1189: \n1190: ```go\n1191: // Example: informer sync test\n1192: func TestInformerSync(t *testing.T) {\n1193:     config := rest.Config{ /* ... */ }\n1194:     cs := versioned.NewForConfigOrDie(config)\n1195:     factory := informers.NewSharedInformerFactory(cs, 0)\n1196:     informer := factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()\n1197:     \n1198:     stopCh := make(chan struct{})\n1199:     defer close(stopCh)\n1200:     factory.Start(stopCh)\n1201:     \n1202:     synced := factory.WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)\n1203:     if !synced[reflect.TypeOf(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{})] {\n1204:         t.Fatal(\"informer did not sync\")\n1205:     }\n1206: }\n1207: ```\n1208: \n1209: ### Test Coverage Targets\n1210: \n1211: | Component | Coverage Target |\n1212: |-----------|-----------------|\n1213: | Clientset constructors | 100% |\n1214: | Typed client CRUD operations | 90% |\n1215: | Informer factory initialization | 85% |\n1216: | Lister operations | 85% |\n1217: | Fake clients | 80% |\n1218: \n1219: ## Code Generation\n1220: \n1221: **Trigger:** `make gen-client` → `hack/update-codegen.sh`\n1222: \n1223: **Dependencies:**\n1224: - `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1\n1225: - `--with-watch` flag enabled\n1226: - Output package: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n1227: \n1228: **Generated markers:**\n1229: ```go\n1230: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen=package\n1231: // +k8s:openapi-gen=true\n1232: // +k8s:defaulter-gen=TypeMeta\n1233: // +groupName=runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n1234: ```\n1235: \n1236: **Regeneration checklist:**\n1237: 1. Update `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n1238: 2. Run `make gen-client`\n1239: 3. Verify generated code compiles\n1240: 4. Run unit tests\n1241: 5. Commit generated files\n1242: \n1243: ## Extension Points\n1244: \n1245: ### Client Expansion\n1246: \n1247: ```go\n1248: // clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go\n1249: type AgentRuntimeExpansion interface {\n1250:     // Add custom methods here\n1251: }\n1252: ```\n1253: \n1254: ### Lister Expansion\n1255: \n1256: ```go\n1257: // listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go\n1258: type AgentRuntimeListerExpansion interface {\n1259:     // Add custom list/query methods here\n1260: }\n1261: ```\n1262: \n1263: ### Informer Customization\n1264: \n1265: ```go\n1266: // Using TweakListOptionsFunc\n1267: factory := informers.NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(\n1268:     clientset,\n1269:     0,\n1270:     informers.WithTweakListOptions(func(opts *metav1.ListOptions) {\n1271:         opts.LabelSelector = \"environment=production\"\n1272:     }),\n1273: )\n1274: ```\n\n(End of file - total 1274 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-005 Sandbox Creation Processor\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the Sandbox processor module within `pkg/workloadmanager`. The processor handles creation and lifecycle management of sandbox environments using Kubernetes custom resources.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── processor/\n│   ├── sandbox_processor.go      # Main processor implementation\n│   ├── sandbox_processor_test.go # Unit tests\n│   └── interface.go              # Processor interface definition\n├── types/\n│   └── sandbox.go                # Sandbox data structures\n└── config/\n    └── sandbox_config.go         # Configuration structures","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775892599365,"end":1775892599394}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892599414,"sessionID":"ses_2848da925ffeSsivYQEgeFrCaj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b7286fa001ZbX8i9RAwaHFNB","messageID":"msg_d7b72757b001IKBzJzZuOh6agq","sessionID":"ses_2848da925ffeSsivYQEgeFrCaj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_204f2d937da04288b3fd33bc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cli-toolkit/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cli-toolkit/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Design\n2: \n3: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`.\n4: \n5: ## Package layout (every module path and role)\n6: \n7: | Path | Role |\n8: |------|------|\n9: | `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n10: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n11: | `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n12: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, all commands, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n13: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n14: | `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n15: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` |\n16: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` |\n17: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` |\n18: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` |\n19: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` |\n20: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |\n21: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` |\n22: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` |\n23: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` |\n24: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` |\n25: | `agentcube/operations/__init__.py` | Placeholder module docstring (no symbols) |\n26: | `examples/hello-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n27: | `examples/math-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n28: \n29: **Setuptools packages** (from `pyproject.toml` `[tool.setuptools]`):  \n30: `agentcube`, `agentcube.cli`, `agentcube.runtime`, `agentcube.operations`, `agentcube.services`  \n31: *(Note: `agentcube.models` is not listed in `[tool.setuptools] packages` but is imported; packaging may rely on setuptools discovery for subpackages — reconstruct imports from source as above.)*\n32: \n33: ## Console script entry point\n34: \n35: ```toml\n36: [project.scripts]\n37: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n38: ```\n39: \n40: Typer app object: `app = typer.Typer(name=\"agentcube\", help=\"...\", no_args_is_help=True, rich_markup_mode=\"rich\", add_completion=False)`.\n41: \n42: ## Typer — root callback\n43: \n44: ```python\n45: def main(\n46:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n47:         None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\",\n48:         callback=version_callback, is_eager=True,\n49:     ),\n50:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n51: ) -> None:\n52:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n53: ```\n54: \n55: ## Typer — `pack`\n56: \n57: ```python\n58: def pack(\n59:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n60:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n61:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n62:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n63:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n64:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n65:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n66:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n67:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n68: ) -> None:\n69: ```\n70: \n71: ## Typer — `build`\n72: \n73: ```python\n74: def build(\n75:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n76:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n77:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n78:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n79:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n80: ) -> None:\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ## Typer — `publish`\n84: \n85: ```python\n86: def publish(\n87:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n88:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n89:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n90:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n91:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n92:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n93:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n94:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n95:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n96:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n97:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n98:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n99:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n100: ) -> None:\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ## Typer — `invoke`\n104: \n105: ```python\n106: def invoke(\n107:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n108:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n109:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n110:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n111:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n112: ) -> None:\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ## Typer — `status`\n116: \n117: ```python\n118: def status(\n119:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n120:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n121:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n122: ) -> None:\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ## Helper functions (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n126: \n127: ```python\n128: def version_callback(value: bool) -> None: ...\n129: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None: ...  # prints, typer.Exit(1)\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ## Runtime classes\n133: \n134: ### `PackRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n135: \n136: ```python\n137: class PackRuntime:\n138:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n139:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n140:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n141:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n142:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n143:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n144:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n145:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n146:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n147:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n148:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n149:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n150:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n151:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n152:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None: ...\n153:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path: ...\n154:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str: ...\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ### `BuildRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n158: \n159: ```python\n160: class BuildRuntime:\n161:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n162:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n163:     def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n164:     def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n165:     def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n166:     def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n167:     def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None: ...\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### `PublishRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`)\n171: \n172: ```python\n173: class PublishRuntime:\n174:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n175:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n176:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n177:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n178:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n179:     def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n180:     def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n181:     def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n182: ```\n183: \n184: ### `InvokeRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n185: \n186: ```python\n187: class InvokeRuntime:\n188:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n189:     def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any: ...\n190:     def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[Any, str, str]: ...\n191:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], endpoint: str, workspace_path: Path) -> Any: ...\n192:     async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n193: ```\n194: \n195: **Implementation note:** `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` only assigns `response` inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`; if the condition is false, `return response` may raise `UnboundLocalError` (as of extracted source).\n196: \n197: ### `StatusRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n198: \n199: ```python\n200: class StatusRuntime:\n201:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n202:     def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n203:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n204:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n205: ```\n206: \n207: ## AR-023: `invoke` command — Technical Implementation\n208: \n209: ### Command Flow\n210: \n211: ```\n212: ┌─────────────────┐     ┌──────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n213: │  CLI (main.py)  │────▶│  InvokeRuntime    │────▶│  HTTP Client    │\n214: │  - parse args   │     │  - validate       │     │  - POST /invoke │\n215: │  - parse JSON   │     │  - build URL      │     │  - headers      │\n216: │  - parse headers│     │  - invoke         │     │  - response     │\n217: └─────────────────┘     └──────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ### CLI Layer (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n221: \n222: **Function signature:**\n223: ```python\n224: def invoke(\n225:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n226:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n227:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n228:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n229:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n230: ) -> None:\n231: ```\n232: \n233: **Implementation:**\n234: ```python\n235: def invoke(\n236:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", ...),\n237:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", ...),\n238:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", ...),\n239:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", ...),\n240:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", ...),\n241: ) -> None:\n242:     import json\n243:     from pathlib import Path\n244:     from rich.console import Console\n245:     from rich.progress import Progress, SpinnerColumn, TextColumn\n246:     \n247:     console = Console()\n248:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).expanduser().resolve()\n249:     \n250:     # Parse payload JSON (early validation)\n251:     try:\n252:         payload_dict = json.loads(payload)\n253:     except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n254:         console.print(f\"[red]Error: Invalid JSON payload: {e}[/red]\")\n255:         raise typer.Exit(1)\n256:     \n257:     # Parse headers\n258:     headers = {}\n259:     if header_list:\n260:         for header in header_list:\n261:             if \":\" not in header:\n262:                 console.print(f\"[red]Error: Invalid header format '{header}'. Expected 'key:value'[/red]\")\n263:                 raise typer.Exit(1)\n264:             key, value = header.split(\":\", 1)\n265:             headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n266:     \n267:     # Execute with progress indicator\n268:     with Progress(\n269:         SpinnerColumn(),\n270:         TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n271:         console=console,\n272:     ) as progress:\n273:         task = progress.add_task(\"Invoking agent...\", total=None)\n274:         try:\n275:             runtime = InvokeRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n276:             result = runtime.invoke(workspace_path, payload_dict, headers if headers else None)\n277:             progress.update(task, completed=True)\n278:             console.print(\"[green]✓ Invocation successful[/green]\")\n279:             # Display result (format based on response type)\n280:             if isinstance(result, dict):\n281:                 console.print_json(json.dumps(result, indent=2))\n282:             else:\n283:                 console.print(result)\n284:         except Exception as e:\n285:             progress.update(task, completed=True)\n286:             _handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)\n287: ```\n288: \n289: ### Runtime Layer (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n290: \n291: **Class structure:**\n292: ```python\n293: import httpx\n294: import asyncio\n295: from pathlib import Path\n296: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional, Tuple\n297: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService\n298: from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\n299: from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\n300: \n301: class InvokeRuntime:\n302:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n303:     \n304:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n305:         self.verbose = verbose\n306:         self.provider = provider\n307:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n308:         self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n309:     \n310:     def invoke(\n311:         self,\n312:         workspace_path: Path,\n313:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n314:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n315:     ) -> Any:\n316:         # Validate prerequisites and get metadata + endpoint\n317:         metadata, endpoint, agent_type = self._validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path)\n318:         \n319:         # Merge session_id from metadata if available\n320:         if headers is None:\n321:             headers = {}\n322:         if metadata.session_id:\n323:             headers[self.SESSION_HEADER] = metadata.session_id\n324:         \n325:         # Route based on provider\n326:         if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n327:             return asyncio.run(\n328:                 self._invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n329:                     agent_id=metadata.agent_id,\n330:                     payload=payload,\n331:                     headers=headers,\n332:                     endpoint=endpoint,\n333:                     workspace_path=workspace_path\n334:                 )\n335:             )\n336:         elif self.provider == \"k8s\":\n337:             return asyncio.run(\n338:                 self._direct_http_invocation(\n339:                     endpoint=endpoint,\n340:                     payload=payload,\n341:                     headers=headers,\n342:                     workspace_path=workspace_path\n343:                 )\n344:             )\n345:         else:\n346:             raise ValueError(f\"Unknown provider: {self.provider}\")\n347:     \n348:     def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(\n349:         self,\n350:         workspace_path: Path\n351:     ) -> Tuple[Any, str, str]:\n352:         \"\"\"Validate workspace and return (metadata, endpoint, agent_type).\"\"\"\n353:         # Load metadata\n354:         metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n355:         \n356:         # Check if published\n357:         if not metadata.agent_id:\n358:             raise ValueError(\n359:                 \"Agent has not been published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\"\n360:             )\n361:         \n362:         # Determine endpoint based on deployment type\n363:         if metadata.k8s_deployment:\n364:             deployment_type = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\", \"unknown\")\n365:             if deployment_type == \"AgentRuntime\":\n366:                 # AgentRuntime CR: construct invocation URL\n367:                 namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n368:                 agent_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"name\", metadata.agent_name)\n369:                 router_url = metadata.router_url or metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"router_url\")\n370:                 if not router_url:\n371:                     raise ValueError(\n372:                         \"router_url is required for AgentRuntime invocation. \"\n373:                         \"Ensure it is set in agent_metadata.yaml\"\n374:                     )\n375:                 endpoint = (\n376:                     f\"{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/\"\n377:                     f\"agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n378:                 )\n379:                 return metadata, endpoint, \"agentruntime\"\n380:             elif deployment_type == \"Deployment\":\n381:                 # Standard K8s Deployment: use agent_endpoint\n382:                 if not metadata.agent_endpoint:\n383:                     raise ValueError(\n384:                         \"agent_endpoint is required for Deployment invocation. \"\n385:                         \"Ensure it is set in agent_metadata.yaml\"\n386:                     )\n387:                 return metadata, metadata.agent_endpoint, \"deployment\"\n388:             else:\n389:                 raise ValueError(f\"Unknown deployment type: {deployment_type}\")\n390:         else:\n391:             # Fallback to agent_endpoint\n392:             if not metadata.agent_endpoint:\n393:                 raise ValueError(\n394:                     \"No agent_endpoint found in metadata. \"\n395:                     \"Agent may not be published correctly.\"\n396:                 )\n397:             return metadata, metadata.agent_endpoint, \"unknown\"\n398:     \n399:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n400:         self,\n401:         agent_id: str,\n402:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n403:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n404:         endpoint: str,\n405:         workspace_path: Path\n406:     ) -> Any:\n407:         \"\"\"Invoke agent through AgentCube Router.\"\"\"\n408:         if not endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):\n409:             # Fix for UnboundLocalError: initialize response\n410:             raise ValueError(f\"Invalid endpoint URL: {endpoint}\")\n411:         \n412:         async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n413:             response = await client.post(\n414:                 endpoint,\n415:                 json=payload,\n416:                 headers=headers,\n417:                 timeout=120.0\n418:             )\n419:             response.raise_for_status()\n420:             return response.json()\n421:     \n422:     async def _direct_http_invocation(\n423:         self,\n424:         endpoint: str,\n425:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n426:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n427:         workspace_path: Path\n428:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n429:         \"\"\"Direct HTTP invocation for standard K8s Deployment.\"\"\"\n430:         async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n431:             response = await client.post(\n432:                 endpoint,\n433:                 json=payload,\n434:                 headers=headers,\n435:                 timeout=120.0\n436:             )\n437:             response.raise_for_status()\n438:             return response.json()\n439: ```\n440: \n441: ### Error Handling\n442: \n443: | Error | Source | CLI Output | Exit Code |\n444: |-------|--------|------------|-----------|\n445: | Invalid JSON payload | `json.loads()` | `[red]Error: Invalid JSON payload: {details}[/red]` | 1 |\n446: | Invalid header format | Header parsing | `[red]Error: Invalid header format '{header}'. Expected 'key:value'[/red]` | 1 |\n447: | Agent not published | `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` | `[red]Error invoking agent: Agent has not been published...[/red]` | 1 |\n448: | Missing router_url | `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` | `[red]Error invoking agent: router_url is required...[/red]` | 1 |\n449: | Missing agent_endpoint | `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` | `[red]Error invoking agent: agent_endpoint is required...[/red]` | 1 |\n450: | HTTP error | `httpx` | `[red]Error invoking agent: {status_code} {reason}[/red]` | 1 |\n451: | Timeout | `httpx.TimeoutException` | `[red]Error invoking agent: Request timed out after 120s[/red]` | 1 |\n452: \n453: ## AR-023: `status` command — Technical Implementation\n454: \n455: ### Command Flow\n456: \n457: ```\n458: ┌─────────────────┐     ┌──────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n459: │  CLI (main.py)  │────▶│  StatusRuntime    │────▶│  Provider       │\n460: │  - parse args   │     │  - get_status     │     │  - K8s API      │\n461: │  - display      │     │  - route          │     │  - CRD API      │\n462: └─────────────────┘     └──────────────────┘     └──────────────────┘\n463:                               │\n464:                               ▼\n465:                        ┌─────────────────┐\n466:                        │  Rich Table     │\n467:                        │  - status       │\n468:                        │  - endpoint     │\n469:                        │  - pods         │\n470:                        └─────────────────┘\n471: ```\n472: \n473: ### CLI Layer (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n474: \n475: **Function signature:**\n476: ```python\n477: def status(\n478:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n479:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n480:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n481: ) -> None:\n482: ```\n483: \n484: **Implementation:**\n485: ```python\n486: def status(\n487:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", ...),\n488:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", ...),\n489:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", ...),\n490: ) -> None:\n491:     from pathlib import Path\n492:     from rich.console import Console\n493:     from rich.table import Table\n494:     from rich.progress import Progress, SpinnerColumn, TextColumn\n495:     \n496:     console = Console()\n497:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).expanduser().resolve()\n498:     \n499:     with Progress(\n500:         SpinnerColumn(),\n501:         TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n502:         console=console,\n503:     ) as progress:\n504:         task = progress.add_task(\"Fetching agent status...\", total=None)\n505:         try:\n506:             runtime = StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n507:             status_info = runtime.get_status(workspace_path, provider=provider)\n508:             progress.update(task, completed=True)\n509:             \n510:             # Check for not_published status\n511:             if status_info.get(\"status\") == \"not_published\":\n512:                 console.print(\"[yellow]⚠ Agent has not been published[/yellow]\")\n513:                 console.print(\n514:                     \"\\nRun [bold]kubectl-agentcube publish[/bold] to deploy your agent.\\n\"\n515:                 )\n516:                 raise typer.Exit(1)\n517:             \n518:             # Check for error status\n519:             if status_info.get(\"status\") == \"error\":\n520:                 console.print(f\"[red]✗ Status error: {status_info.get('error', 'Unknown error')}[/red]\")\n521:                 raise typer.Exit(1)\n522:             \n523:             # Display status table\n524:             table = Table(title=f\"Agent Status: {status_info.get('agent_name', 'Unknown')}\")\n525:             table.add_column(\"Property\", style=\"cyan\")\n526:             table.add_column(\"Value\", style=\"green\")\n527:             \n528:             # Core status\n529:             table.add_row(\"Status\", status_info.get(\"status\", \"unknown\"))\n530:             if status_info.get(\"agent_endpoint\"):\n531:                 table.add_row(\"Endpoint\", status_info[\"agent_endpoint\"])\n532:             if status_info.get(\"deployment_type\"):\n533:                 table.add_row(\"Deployment Type\", status_info[\"deployment_type\"])\n534:             if status_info.get(\"namespace\"):\n535:                 table.add_row(\"Namespace\", status_info[\"namespace\"])\n536:             \n537:             # Pod status (if available)\n538:             if \"pods\" in status_info:\n539:                 pod_info = status_info[\"pods\"]\n540:                 table.add_row(\n541:                     \"Pods\",\n542:                     f\"{pod_info.get('ready', 0)}/{pod_info.get('total', 0)} ready\"\n543:                 )\n544:             \n545:             # Replicas (for K8s deployment)\n546:             if status_info.get(\"replicas\") is not None:\n547:                 table.add_row(\"Replicas\", str(status_info[\"replicas\"]))\n548:             \n549:             # Session info (if available)\n550:             if status_info.get(\"session_id\"):\n551:                 table.add_row(\"Session ID\", status_info[\"session_id\"])\n552:             \n553:             console.print(table)\n554:             \n555:         except Exception as e:\n556:             progress.update(task, completed=True)\n557:             _handle_error(e, \"fetching status\", verbose)\n558: ```\n559: \n560: ### Runtime Layer (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n561: \n562: **Class structure:**\n563: ```python\n564: import logging\n565: from pathlib import Path\n566: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n567: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService\n568: from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\n569: from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\n570: \n571: class StatusRuntime:\n572:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n573:         self.verbose = verbose\n574:         self.provider = provider\n575:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n576:         self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n577:     \n578:     def get_status(\n579:         self,\n580:         workspace_path: Path,\n581:         provider: Optional[str] = None\n582:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n583:         \"\"\"Get comprehensive agent status.\"\"\"\n584:         if provider is None:\n585:             provider = self.provider\n586:         \n587:         # Load metadata\n588:         try:\n589:             metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n590:         except FileNotFoundError:\n591:             return {\n592:                 \"status\": \"not_found\",\n593:                 \"error\": f\"Metadata not found at {workspace_path}\"\n594:             }\n595:         \n596:         # Check if published\n597:         if not metadata.agent_id:\n598:             return {\n599:                 \"status\": \"not_published\",\n600:                 \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name\n601:             }\n602:         \n603:         # Build base status\n604:         status_info = {\n605:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n606:             \"agent_id\": metadata.agent_id,\n607:             \"session_id\": metadata.session_id,\n608:             \"deployment_type\": metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\", \"unknown\") if metadata.k8s_deployment else \"unknown\",\n609:             \"namespace\": metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\") if metadata.k8s_deployment else \"default\",\n610:         }\n611:         \n612:         # Route to appropriate status getter\n613:         if metadata.k8s_deployment:\n614:             deployment_type = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\", \"unknown\")\n615:             if deployment_type == \"AgentRuntime\":\n616:                 cr_status = self._get_cr_k8s_status(metadata)\n617:                 status_info.update(cr_status)\n618:             elif deployment_type == \"Deployment\":\n619:                 k8s_status = self._get_k8s_status(metadata)\n620:                 status_info.update(k8s_status)\n621:             else:\n622:                 status_info[\"status\"] = \"unknown_deployment_type\"\n623:         else:\n624:             status_info[\"status\"] = \"unknown\"\n625:         \n626:         return status_info\n627:     \n628:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n629:         \"\"\"Get status for standard K8s Deployment.\"\"\"\n630:         try:\n631:             k8s_provider = KubernetesProvider(\n632:                 namespace=metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\"),\n633:                 verbose=self.verbose\n634:             )\n635:             \n636:             deployment_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"deployment_name\")\n637:             if not deployment_name:\n638:                 return {\"status\": \"error\", \"error\": \"deployment_name not found in metadata\"}\n639:             \n640:             # Get deployment status\n641:             deployment_info = k8s_provider.get_agent_status(deployment_name)\n642:             \n643:             # Extract pod information\n644:             pods = deployment_info.get(\"pods\", [])\n645:             ready_pods = sum(1 for p in pods if p.get(\"ready\", False))\n646:             \n647:             return {\n648:                 \"status\": deployment_info.get(\"status\", \"unknown\"),\n649:                 \"agent_endpoint\": metadata.agent_endpoint,\n650:                 \"replicas\": deployment_info.get(\"replicas\", 1),\n651:                 \"pods\": {\n652:                     \"total\": len(pods),\n653:                     \"ready\": ready_pods,\n654:                     \"details\": pods\n655:                 }\n656:             }\n657:         except Exception as e:\n658:             self.logger.error(f\"Error getting K8s status: {e}\")\n659:             return {\n660:                 \"status\": \"error\",\n661:                 \"error\": str(e)\n662:             }\n663:     \n664:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n665:         \"\"\"Get status for AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n666:         try:\n667:             agentcube_provider = AgentCubeProvider(\n668:                 namespace=metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\"),\n669:                 verbose=self.verbose\n670:             )\n671:             \n672:             agent_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"name\", metadata.agent_name)\n673:             \n674:             # Get AgentRuntime CR\n675:             cr_object = agentcube_provider.get_agent_runtime(\n676:                 name=agent_name,\n677:                 namespace=metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n678:             )\n679:             \n680:             if cr_object is None:\n681:                 return {\n682:                     \"status\": \"not_found\",\n683:                     \"error\": f\"AgentRuntime '{agent_name}' not found in namespace '{metadata.k8s_deployment.get('namespace', 'default')}'\"\n684:                 }\n685:             \n686:             # Extract status from CR\n687:             cr_status = cr_object.get(\"status\", {})\n688:             status = cr_status.get(\"status\", \"created_no_status\")\n689:             endpoint = cr_status.get(\"agentEndpoint\", metadata.agent_endpoint)\n690:             \n691:             return {\n692:                 \"status\": status,\n693:                 \"agent_endpoint\": endpoint,\n694:                 \"session_id\": metadata.session_id,\n695:             }\n696:         except Exception as e:\n697:             self.logger.error(f\"Error getting CR status: {e}\")\n698:             return {\n699:                 \"status\": \"error\",\n700:                 \"error\": str(e)\n701:             }\n702: ```\n703: \n704: ### Status Response Schema\n705: \n706: ```python\n707: # Successful status response (AgentRuntime CR)\n708: {\n709:     \"agent_name\": \"hello-agent\",\n710:     \"agent_id\": \"agent-12345\",\n711:     \"session_id\": \"session-abcde\",\n712:     \"status\": \"ready\",  # ready, pending, error, not_found\n713:     \"agent_endpoint\": \"http://router.example.com/v1/...\",\n714:     \"deployment_type\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n715:     \"namespace\": \"default\"\n716: }\n717: \n718: # Successful status response (K8s Deployment)\n719: {\n720:     \"agent_name\": \"hello-agent\",\n721:     \"agent_id\": \"agent-12345\",\n722:     \"session_id\": \"session-abcde\",\n723:     \"status\": \"ready\",\n724:     \"agent_endpoint\": \"http://node:30080\",\n725:     \"deployment_type\": \"Deployment\",\n726:     \"namespace\": \"default\",\n727:     \"replicas\": 1,\n728:     \"pods\": {\n729:         \"total\": 1,\n730:         \"ready\": 1,\n731:         \"details\": [\n732:             {\"name\": \"hello-agent-xxx\", \"ready\": True, \"phase\": \"Running\"}\n733:         ]\n734:     }\n735: }\n736: \n737: # Not published response\n738: {\n739:     \"status\": \"not_published\",\n740:     \"agent_name\": \"hello-agent\"\n741: }\n742: \n743: # Error response\n744: {\n745:     \"status\": \"error\",\n746:     \"error\": \"Docker is not available\"\n747: }\n748: ```\n749: \n750: ### Error Handling\n751: \n752: | Error | Source | CLI Output | Exit Code |\n753: |-------|--------|------------|-----------|\n754: | Metadata not found | `MetadataService.load_metadata` | `[red]Error fetching status: Metadata not found at {path}[/red]` | 1 |\n755: | Agent not published | `get_status` check | `[yellow]⚠ Agent has not been published[/yellow]` + guidance | 1 |\n756: | CR not found | `_get_cr_k8s_status` | `[red]Error fetching status: AgentRuntime 'xxx' not found...[/red]` | 1 |\n757: | K8s API error | `KubernetesProvider` | `[red]Error fetching status: {error}[/red]` | 1 |\n758: | Status error | CR/Deployment status | `[red]✗ Status error: {error}[/red]` | 1 |\n759: \n760: ## `DockerService` (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n761: \n762: ```python\n763: class DockerService:\n764:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n765:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n766:     def build_image(\n767:         self,\n768:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n769:         context_path: Path,\n770:         image_name: str,\n771:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n772:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n773:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n774:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n775:     def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n776:     def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str: ...\n777:     def push_image(\n778:         self,\n779:         image_name: str,\n780:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n781:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n782:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n783:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n784:     def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None: ...\n785:     def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None: ...\n786:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n787: ```\n788: \n789: ## `MetadataService` (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n790: \n791: ```python\n792: class MetadataService:\n793:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n794:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n795:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n796:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n797:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool: ...\n798:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n799:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n800: ```\n801: \n802: ## `KubernetesProvider` (`agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`)\n803: \n804: ```python\n805: class KubernetesProvider:\n806:     def __init__(\n807:         self,\n808:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n809:         verbose: bool = False,\n810:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n811:     ) -> None: ...\n812:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n813:     def deploy_agent(\n814:         self,\n815:         agent_name: str,\n816:         image_url: str,\n817:         port: int,\n818:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n819:         replicas: int = 1,\n820:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n821:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n822:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n823:     def _create_deployment(\n824:         self,\n825:         name: str,\n826:         image_url: str,\n827:         port: int,\n828:         entrypoint: Optional[str],\n829:         replicas: int,\n830:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n831:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n832:     def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n833:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n834:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n835:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n836:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n837: ```\n838: \n839: ## `AgentCubeProvider` (`agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`)\n840: \n841: ```python\n842: class AgentCubeProvider:\n843:     def __init__(\n844:         self,\n845:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n846:         verbose: bool = False,\n847:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n848:     ) -> None: ...\n849:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n850:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n851:         self,\n852:         agent_name: str,\n853:         image_url: str,\n854:         port: int,\n855:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n856:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n857:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n858:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n859:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n860:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n861:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n862:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n863:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n864: ```\n865: \n866: CR API: `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`.\n867: \n868: ## `AgentMetadata` (Pydantic `BaseModel`)\n869: \n870: | Field | Type | Default | `Field(..., description=...)` |\n871: |-------|------|---------|--------------------------------|\n872: | `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n873: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n874: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n875: | `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n876: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n877: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n878: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n879: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string for publishing |\n880: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image information |\n881: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication configuration |\n882: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n883: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for image publishing |\n884: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n885: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n886: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n887: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Workload Manager |\n888: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Router |\n889: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path for the readiness probe |\n890: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port for the readiness probe |\n891: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n892: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The session ID for the agent |\n893: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment information |\n894: \n895: Validators: `validate_language` → `['python','java']` lowercase; `validate_build_mode` → `['local','cloud']` lowercase; `validate_port` → `1..65535`.\n896: \n897: ## `MetadataOptions` (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n898: \n899: Dataclass fields (all `Optional` unless noted):\n900: \n901: | Field | Type | Default |\n902: |-------|------|---------|\n903: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n904: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n905: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n906: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n907: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n908: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n909: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n910: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n911: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n912: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n913: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n914: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n915: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n916: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n917: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n918: \n919: ```python\n920: @classmethod\n921: def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\": ...\n922: ```\n923: \n924: ## Dependencies (`cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`)\n925: \n926: **`[project]` dependencies:**\n927: \n928: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0`\n929: - `pydantic>=2.0.0`\n930: - `pyyaml>=6.0`\n931: - `httpx>=0.24.0`\n932: - `docker>=6.0.0`\n933: - `rich>=13.0.0`\n934: - `packaging>=23.0`\n935: - `importlib-resources>=6.0.0`\n936: - `semver>=3.0.0`\n937: \n938: **Optional `[project.optional-dependencies]`:**\n939: \n940: - `k8s`: `kubernetes>=28.0.0`\n941: - `dev`: `pytest>=7.4.0`, `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0`, `pytest-cov>=4.1.0`, `ruff>=0.1.0`, `mypy>=1.5.0`, `pre-commit>=3.3.0`, `kubernetes>=28.0.0`\n942: - `test`: `pytest>=7.4.0`, `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0`, `pytest-cov>=4.1.0`, `pytest-mock>=3.11.0`, `httpx-mock>=0.10.0`\n943: \n944: **Python:** `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`.\n945: \n946: ## Top-level exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n947: \n948: - `__version__ = \"0.1.0\"`\n949: - `__author__ = \"AgentCube Community\"`\n950: - `__email__ = \"agentcube@volcano.sh\"`\n951: - Imports: `app`, `PackRuntime`, `BuildRuntime`, `PublishRuntime`, `InvokeRuntime`\n952: - `__all__` = `[\"app\", \"PackRuntime\", \"BuildRuntime\", \"PublishRuntime\", \"InvokeRuntime\"]`  \n953:   (`StatusRuntime` is not exported here.)\n\n(End of file - total 953 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Design\n\nSource root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`.\n\n## Package layout (every module path and role)\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n| `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, all commands, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cli-toolkit/design.md","time":{"start":1775892599370,"end":1775892599411}}}}
