{"type":"text","timestamp":1775892627928,"sessionID":"ses_2848da925ffeSsivYQEgeFrCaj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b72f9d9001AWSwuyAqvUYkp3","messageID":"msg_d7b72e4fa001WkPSA5QBLXU5l2","sessionID":"ses_2848da925ffeSsivYQEgeFrCaj","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the context needed. Let me write the design.md file for AR-042:","time":{"start":1775892627924,"end":1775892627924}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892741867,"sessionID":"ses_2848da925ffeSsivYQEgeFrCaj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b7301d600174XeX7j1lEBo6x","messageID":"msg_d7b72e4fa001WkPSA5QBLXU5l2","sessionID":"ses_2848da925ffeSsivYQEgeFrCaj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_757db98578b74c68934d1d73","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/design.md","content":"# Design: AR-042 — Docusaurus 文档站框架\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation of a Docusaurus v3-based documentation site for the AgentCube project. The documentation framework provides a unified, maintainable, and extensible platform for technical documentation with support for versioning, internationalization (i18n), search, and automated deployment.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\ndocs/\n├── .gitignore                        # Git ignore for build artifacts\n├── README.md                         # Documentation for working with docs\n├── package.json                      # NPM dependencies and scripts\n├── tsconfig.json                     # TypeScript configuration\n├── docusaurus.config.ts              # Docusaurus site configuration\n├── sidebars.ts                       # Documentation sidebar configuration\n├── docs/                             # Markdown documentation files\n│   ├── intro/                        # Introduction documents\n│   ├── concepts/                     # Core concepts\n│   ├── crd-reference/                # CRD API reference\n│   ├── api-reference/                # REST API reference\n│   ├── sdk-cli/                      # SDK and CLI usage\n│   ├── deployment/                   # Deployment guides\n│   ├── configuration/                # Configuration reference\n│   ├── observability/                # Monitoring and logging\n│   ├── troubleshooting/              # FAQ and troubleshooting\n│   ├── requirements/                 # Architecture requirements (AR-001 ~ AR-042)\n│   └── contributing/                 # Contribution guidelines\n├── src/                              # Custom React components\n│   ├── components/                   # Reusable components\n│   │   ├── CRDTable/                 # CRD field table component\n│   │   └── ArchitectureDiagram/      # Architecture diagram component\n│   ├── css/                          # Custom CSS styles\n│   │   └── custom.css\n│   └── pages/                        # Custom pages\n│       └── index.tsx                 # Home page\n├── static/                           # Static assets\n│   ├── img/                          # Images and logos\n│   │   └── logo.svg\n│   ├── favicon.ico\n│   └── robots.txt\n└── i18n/                             # Internationalization (future)\n    ├── zh/                           # Chinese (default)\n    └── en/                           # English (future)\n```\n\n### Integration Points\n\n- **GitHub Pages**: Automated deployment via GitHub Actions\n- **Algolia DocSearch**: Full-text search integration (optional)\n- **GitHub Discussions**: Community links in navigation\n- **Volcano Project**: Reference documentation and branding alignment\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Docusaurus Config (`docusaurus.config.ts`)\n\n```typescript\ninterface Config {\n  title: string;                      // Site title: \"AgentCube\"\n  tagline: string;                    // Site description\n  favicon: string;                    // Path to favicon\n  url: string;                        // Production URL\n  baseUrl: string;                    // Base path: \"/agentcube/\"\n  organizationName: string;           // GitHub org: \"volcano-sh\"\n  projectName: string;                // GitHub repo: \"agentcube\"\n  onBrokenLinks: 'throw' | 'warn';    // Link validation behavior\n  onBrokenMarkdownLinks: 'throw' | 'warn';\n  \n  i18n: {\n    defaultLocale: string;            // \"zh\"\n    locales: string[];                // [\"zh\", \"en\"]\n    localeConfigs: Record<string, {\n      htmlLang: string;\n      label: string;\n    }>;\n  };\n  \n  presets: [\n    '@docusaurus/preset-classic',\n    {\n      docs: DocsOptions;\n      blog: false;\n      theme: ThemeOptions;\n    }\n  ];\n  \n  themeConfig: {\n    navbar: NavbarConfig;\n    footer: FooterConfig;\n    prism: PrismConfig;\n    algolia?: AlgoliaConfig;\n  };\n}\n```\n\n### Package Dependencies (`package.json`)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"agentcube-docs\",\n  \"version\": \"0.2.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"start\": \"docusaurus start\",\n    \"build\": \"docusaurus build\",\n    \"serve\": \"docusaurus serve\",\n    \"deploy\": \"docusaurus deploy\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@docusaurus/core\": \"^3.6.0\",\n    \"@docusaurus/preset-classic\": \"^3.6.0\",\n    \"@mdx-js/react\": \"^3.0.0\",\n    \"clsx\": \"^2.1.0\",\n    \"prism-react-renderer\": \"^2.3.0\",\n    \"react\": \"^18.2.0\",\n    \"react-dom\": \"^18.2.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@docusaurus/module-type-aliases\": \"^3.6.0\",\n    \"@docusaurus/tsconfig\": \"^3.6.0\",\n    \"@docusaurus/types\": \"^3.6.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"~5.3.3\"\n  },\n  \"engines\": {\n    \"node\": \">=18.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Sidebar Configuration (`sidebars.ts`)\n\n```typescript\ninterface SidebarsConfig {\n  tutorialSidebar: SidebarItem[];\n}\n\ntype SidebarItem = \n  | SidebarCategory\n  | SidebarDoc\n  | SidebarLink;\n\ninterface SidebarCategory {\n  type: 'category';\n  label: string;\n  link?: {\n    type: 'doc';\n    id: string;\n  };\n  items: string[];\n}\n```\n\n### Custom Component Props\n\n```typescript\n// CRDTable Component\ninterface CRDTableProps {\n  crdName: string;\n  fields: FieldSpec[];\n}\n\ninterface FieldSpec {\n  name: string;\n  type: string;\n  required: boolean;\n  description: string;\n}\n\n// ArchitectureDiagram Component\ninterface ArchitectureDiagramProps {\n  src: string;\n  alt: string;\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### NPM Scripts\n\n| Script | Command | Description | Exit Code |\n|--------|---------|-------------|-----------|\n| `start` | `docusaurus start` | Start dev server at localhost:3000 | 0 on success, 1 on error |\n| `build` | `docusaurus build` | Generate static build into `build/` | 0 on success, 1 on error |\n| `serve` | `docusaurus serve` | Serve production build locally | 0 on success, 1 on error |\n| `deploy` | `docusaurus deploy` | Deploy to GitHub Pages | 0 on success, 1 on error |\n| `typecheck` | `tsc` | Type-check TypeScript files | 0 if no errors, 1 on errors |\n\n### Configuration Validation\n\n```typescript\n// docusaurus.config.ts validation\nconst config: Config = {\n  // Required fields\n  title: 'AgentCube',                    // Must be non-empty string\n  tagline: 'Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration for AI agents',\n  url: 'https://volcano-sh.github.io',   // Must be valid URL\n  baseUrl: '/agentcube/',                // Must start and end with /\n  organizationName: 'volcano-sh',        // GitHub organization\n  projectName: 'agentcube',              // GitHub repository\n  \n  // Optional but recommended\n  onBrokenLinks: 'throw',                // Fail build on broken links\n  onBrokenMarkdownLinks: 'warn',\n  \n  // i18n configuration\n  i18n: {\n    defaultLocale: 'zh',\n    locales: ['zh', 'en'],\n  },\n};\n```\n\n### Deployment Workflow\n\n```yaml\n# GitHub Actions: .github/workflows/docs.yml\nname: Deploy Documentation\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n    paths: ['docs/**']\n  workflow_dispatch:\n\njobs:\n  deploy:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    defaults:\n      run:\n        working-directory: ./docs\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - name: Setup Node.js\n        uses: actions/setup-node@v4\n        with:\n          node-version: '18'\n          cache: 'npm'\n          cache-dependency-path: docs/package-lock.json\n      - name: Install dependencies\n        run: npm ci\n      - name: Build documentation\n        run: npm run build\n      - name: Deploy to GitHub Pages\n        uses: peaceiris/actions-gh-pages@v4\n        with:\n          github_token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n          publish_dir: ./docs/build\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Build Errors\n\n| Error | Source | CLI Output | Resolution |\n|-------|--------|------------|------------|\n| Broken links | Markdown links to non-existent files | `Error: Broken link to ./missing.md` | Fix or remove broken link |\n| Missing sidebar item | Sidebar references non-existent doc | `Error: Sidebar item not found: intro/missing` | Add doc or update sidebar |\n| TypeScript errors | Invalid config types | `TS2322: Type '...' is not assignable` | Fix type mismatch |\n| Missing dependencies | package.json not installed | `Error: Cannot find module '@docusaurus/core'` | Run `npm install` |\n| Node version mismatch | Node < 18 | `Error: Node.js 18+ required` | Upgrade Node.js |\n\n### Runtime Errors (Dev Server)\n\n| Error | Source | CLI Output | Resolution |\n|-------|--------|------------|------------|\n| Port in use | localhost:3000 occupied | `Error: Port 3000 is already in use` | Use different port or kill process |\n| Invalid MDX | Malformed MDX syntax | `SyntaxError: Unexpected token` | Fix MDX syntax |\n| Missing import | Import path doesn't exist | `Error: Cannot find module './Component'` | Fix import path |\n\n### Deployment Errors\n\n| Error | Source | GitHub Actions Output | Resolution |\n|-------|--------|----------------------|------------|\n| Build timeout | Build > 10 minutes | `Error: The operation was canceled` | Optimize build, check for infinite loops |\n| Permission denied | GitHub token issue | `Error: Permission denied` | Check repository permissions |\n| Disk space | Insufficient runner disk space | `Error: No space left on device` | Clean up build artifacts |\n\n### Error Boundaries\n\n```typescript\n// Custom error boundary for React components\nimport React from 'react';\n\nexport class ErrorBoundary extends React.Component<\n  {children: React.ReactNode},\n  {hasError: boolean}\n> {\n  constructor(props: {children: React.ReactNode}) {\n    super(props);\n    this.state = {hasError: false};\n  }\n\n  static getDerivedStateFromError() {\n    return {hasError: true};\n  }\n\n  render() {\n    if (this.state.hasError) {\n      return <div>Component failed to load</div>;\n    }\n    return this.props.children;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**File**: `docs/src/components/__tests__/`\n\n| Test Case | Component | Description |\n|-----------|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestCRDTable_RendersFields` | CRDTable | Verify all fields render correctly |\n| `TestCRDTable_RequiredIndicator` | CRDTable | Verify required fields show ✅ |\n| `TestArchitectureDiagram_AltText` | ArchitectureDiagram | Verify alt text is accessible |\n| `TestArchitectureDiagram_ImageSrc` | ArchitectureDiagram | Verify image source is correct |\n\n```typescript\n// Example: CRDTable test\nimport React from 'react';\nimport {render} from '@testing-library/react';\nimport {CRDTable} from '../CRDTable';\n\ndescribe('CRDTable', () => {\n  it('renders all fields correctly', () => {\n    const fields = [\n      {name: 'image', type: 'string', required: true, description: 'Container image'},\n      {name: 'command', type: 'string[]', required: false, description: 'Command'},\n    ];\n    \n    const {getByText} = render(\n      <CRDTable crdName=\"AgentRuntime\" fields={fields} />\n    );\n    \n    expect(getByText('image')).toBeInTheDocument();\n    expect(getByText('string')).toBeInTheDocument();\n    expect(getByText('Container image')).toBeInTheDocument();\n  });\n});\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**File**: `docs/__tests__/integration/`\n\n| Test Case | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestBuild_Success` | Production build completes without errors |\n| `TestDevServer_Start` | Development server starts on localhost:3000 |\n| `TestNavigation_Links` | All sidebar links navigate correctly |\n| `TestSearch_Functionality` | Search returns expected results (if Algolia configured) |\n| `TestMobile_Responsive` | Site is responsive on mobile viewports |\n\n```bash\n# Integration test script\n#!/bin/bash\nset -e\n\necho \"Running integration tests...\"\n\n# Test 1: Build succeeds\necho \"Testing build...\"\nnpm run build\nif [ $? -ne 0 ]; then\n  echo \"❌ Build failed\"\n  exit 1\nfi\necho \"✅ Build succeeded\"\n\n# Test 2: Serve works\necho \"Testing serve...\"\nnpm run serve &\nSERVE_PID=$!\nsleep 5\ncurl -s http://localhost:3000 > /dev/null\nif [ $? -ne 0 ]; then\n  echo \"❌ Serve failed\"\n  kill $SERVE_PID\n  exit 1\nfi\nkill $SERVE_PID\necho \"✅ Serve succeeded\"\n\n# Test 3: Links are valid\necho \"Testing links...\"\nnpm run build -- --skip-build\n# Use link checker tool\necho \"✅ Links valid\"\n\necho \"All integration tests passed!\"\n```\n\n### Visual Regression Tests\n\n**Tool**: Playwright or Percy (optional)\n\n```typescript\n// Example: Playwright visual test\nimport {test, expect} from '@playwright/test';\n\ntest('homepage should match screenshot', async ({page}) => {\n  await page.goto('http://localhost:3000');\n  await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot('homepage.png');\n});\n\ntest('documentation page should match screenshot', async ({page}) => {\n  await page.goto('http://localhost:3000/docs/intro/01-overview');\n  await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot('docs-overview.png');\n});\n```\n\n### Accessibility Tests\n\n**Tool**: axe-core or Lighthouse CI\n\n```bash\n# Lighthouse CI configuration\n# docs/.lighthouserc.json\n{\n  \"ci\": {\n    \"collect\": {\n      \"staticDistDir\": \"./build\",\n      \"url\": [\n        \"http://localhost/agentcube/\",\n        \"http://localhost/agentcube/docs/intro/01-overview\"\n      ]\n    },\n    \"assert\": {\n      \"assertions\": {\n        \"accessibility\": [\"error\", {\"minScore\": 0.9}]\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Test Coverage Targets\n\n| Component | Coverage Target |\n|-----------|-----------------|\n| Custom React components | 90% |\n| Configuration files | 100% |\n| Documentation content | N/A (manual review) |\n| CI/CD pipeline | 100% (all steps must pass) |\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```typescript\n// docs/__fixtures__/crd-data.ts\nexport const sampleAgentRuntimeFields = [\n  {name: 'image', type: 'string', required: true, description: 'Container image'},\n  {name: 'command', type: 'string[]', required: false, description: 'Container command'},\n  {name: 'sessionTimeout', type: 'string', required: false, description: 'Session TTL'},\n  {name: 'resources', type: 'ResourceRequirements', required: false, description: 'Resource limits'},\n];\n\nexport const sampleCodeInterpreterFields = [\n  {name: 'runtime', type: 'string', required: true, description: 'Runtime type'},\n  {name: 'version', type: 'string', required: false, description: 'Runtime version'},\n  {name: 'sandbox', type: 'SandboxSpec', required: false, description: 'Sandbox configuration'},\n];\n```\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### File Generation\n\n```bash\n# Initialize Docusaurus project\ncd docs\nnpx create-docusaurus@latest . classic --typescript\n\n# Install additional dependencies\nnpm install --save-dev @docusaurus/module-type-aliases @docusaurus/tsconfig\n\n# Create directory structure\nmkdir -p docs/{intro,concepts,crd-reference,api-reference,sdk-cli,deployment,configuration,observability,troubleshooting,requirements,contributing}\nmkdir -p src/{components,css,pages}\nmkdir -p static/{img}\nmkdir -p __tests__/{unit,integration}\n```\n\n### Configuration Steps\n\n1. **Update `docusaurus.config.ts`**:\n   - Set `title`, `tagline`, `url`, `baseUrl`\n   - Configure GitHub organization and project\n   - Set up i18n locales\n   - Configure navbar and footer\n   - Add Algolia search (optional)\n\n2. **Update `sidebars.ts`**:\n   - Define sidebar categories\n   - Add document IDs in order\n   - Configure category links\n\n3. **Create `package.json` scripts**:\n   - `start`: Development server\n   - `build`: Production build\n   - `serve`: Local production serve\n   - `deploy`: GitHub Pages deployment\n\n4. **Create `.gitignore`**:\n   ```\n   node_modules/\n   build/\n   .docusaurus/\n   *.log\n   ```\n\n### Custom Component Implementation\n\n#### CRDTable Component\n\n```typescript\n// src/components/CRDTable/index.tsx\nimport React from 'react';\nimport styles from './styles.module.css';\n\ninterface FieldSpec {\n  name: string;\n  type: string;\n  required: boolean;\n  description: string;\n}\n\ninterface CRDTableProps {\n  crdName: string;\n  fields: FieldSpec[];\n}\n\nexport function CRDTable({crdName, fields}: CRDTableProps) {\n  return (\n    <div className={styles.crdTable}>\n      <h3>{crdName}</h3>\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>Field</th>\n            <th>Type</th>\n            <th>Required</th>\n            <th>Description</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          {fields.map((field) => (\n            <tr key={field.name}>\n              <td><code>{field.name}</code></td>\n              <td><code>{field.type}</code></td>\n              <td>{field.required ? '✅' : '❌'}</td>\n              <td>{field.description}</td>\n            </tr>\n          ))}\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\nexport default CRDTable;\n```\n\n```css\n/* src/components/CRDTable/styles.module.css */\n.crdTable {\n  margin: 2rem 0;\n  overflow-x: auto;\n}\n\n.crdTable table {\n  width: 100%;\n  border-collapse: collapse;\n}\n\n.crdTable th,\n.crdTable td {\n  padding: 0.75rem;\n  border: 1px solid var(--ifm-color-emphasis-300);\n}\n\n.crdTable th {\n  background-color: var(--ifm-color-emphasis-100);\n  font-weight: bold;\n}\n\n.crdTable code {\n  font-size: 0.9em;\n}\n```\n\n#### ArchitectureDiagram Component\n\n```typescript\n// src/components/ArchitectureDiagram/index.tsx\nimport React from 'react';\nimport styles from './styles.module.css';\n\ninterface ArchitectureDiagramProps {\n  src: string;\n  alt: string;\n}\n\nexport function ArchitectureDiagram({src, alt}: ArchitectureDiagramProps) {\n  return (\n    <div className={styles.diagramContainer}>\n      <img src={src} alt={alt} className={styles.diagram} />\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\nexport default ArchitectureDiagram;\n```\n\n### Documentation Content Structure\n\nEach documentation category follows a consistent structure:\n\n```markdown\n---\nsidebar_label: Overview\ntitle: AgentCube Overview\ndescription: Introduction to AgentCube\n---\n\n# AgentCube Overview\n\n## What is AgentCube?\n\n[Content here]\n\n## Key Features\n\n| Feature | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| Feature 1 | Description |\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n[Architecture diagram]\n```\n\n## Quick Links\n\n- [Link 1](./doc2.md)\n- [Link 2](../other/doc.md)\n```\n\n### Versioning Strategy (Future)\n\n```typescript\n// docusaurus.config.ts versioning\npresets: [\n  [\n    'classic',\n    {\n      docs: {\n        sidebarPath: './sidebars.ts',\n        versions: {\n          current: {\n            label: 'v0.2.x (Development)',\n          },\n          '0.1.x': {\n            label: 'v0.1.x (Stable)',\n          },\n        },\n        showLastUpdateTime: true,\n        showLastUpdateAuthor: true,\n      },\n    },\n  ],\n],\n```\n\n### Internationalization Strategy (Future)\n\n```typescript\n// docusaurus.config.ts i18n\ni18n: {\n  defaultLocale: 'zh',\n  locales: ['zh', 'en'],\n  localeConfigs: {\n    zh: {\n      htmlLang: 'zh-CN',\n      label: '简体中文',\n    },\n    en: {\n      htmlLang: 'en-US',\n      label: 'English',\n    },\n  },\n},\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```json\n{\n  \"runtime\": {\n    \"@docusaurus/core\": \"^3.6.0\",\n    \"@docusaurus/preset-classic\": \"^3.6.0\",\n    \"@mdx-js/react\": \"^3.0.0\",\n    \"react\": \"^18.2.0\",\n    \"react-dom\": \"^18.2.0\"\n  },\n  \"dev\": {\n    \"@docusaurus/module-type-aliases\": \"^3.6.0\",\n    \"@docusaurus/tsconfig\": \"^3.6.0\",\n    \"@docusaurus/types\": \"^3.6.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"~5.3.3\",\n    \"@testing-library/react\": \"^14.0.0\",\n    \"@playwright/test\": \"^1.40.0\"\n  },\n  \"optional\": {\n    \"@docusaurus/plugin-content-blog\": \"^3.6.0\",\n    \"@docusaurus/plugin-ideal-image\": \"^3.6.0\",\n    \"@easyops-cn/docusaurus-search-local\": \"^0.40.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\nagentcube/\n├── docs/\n│   ├── .gitignore                    # Git ignore for build artifacts\n│   ├── README.md                     # Documentation for working with docs\n│   ├── package.json                  # NPM dependencies and scripts\n│   ├── package-lock.json             # Locked dependency versions\n│   ├── tsconfig.json                 # TypeScript configuration\n│   ├── docusaurus.config.ts          # Docusaurus site configuration\n│   ├── sidebars.ts                   # Documentation sidebar configuration\n│   ├── docs/\n│   │   ├── intro/\n│   │   │   ├── _category_.json       # Category configuration\n│   │   │   ├── 01-overview.md        # Introduction documentation\n│   │   │   ├── 02-features.md        # Features documentation\n│   │   │   └── 03-quickstart.md      # Quick start guide\n│   │   ├── concepts/\n│   │   │   ├── _category_.json\n│   │   │   ├── 01-agent-runtime.md\n│   │   │   ├── 02-code-interpreter.md\n│   │   │   └── 03-router.md\n│   │   ├── crd-reference/\n│   │   │   ├── _category_.json\n│   │   │   ├── agent-runtime.md\n│   │   │   └── code-interpreter.md\n│   │   └── requirements/\n│   │       ├── _category_.json\n│   │       ├── ar-001.md\n│   │       └── ar-002.md\n│   ├── src/\n│   │   ├── components/\n│   │   │   ├── CRDTable/\n│   │   │   │   ├── index.tsx\n│   │   │   │   └── styles.module.css\n│   │   │   └── ArchitectureDiagram/\n│   │   │       ├── index.tsx\n│   │   │       └── styles.module.css\n│   │   ├── css/\n│   │   │   └── custom.css\n│   │   └── pages/\n│   │       └── index.tsx\n│   ├── static/\n│   │   ├── img/\n│   │   │   ├── logo.svg\n│   │   │   └── favicon.ico\n│   │   └── robots.txt\n│   ├── __tests__/\n│   │   ├── unit/\n│   │   └── integration/\n│   └── scripts/\n│       └── check-ar-docs.sh            # AR documentation coverage checker\n└── .github/\n    └── workflows/\n        └── docs.yml                    # GitHub Actions deployment\n```\n\n## Environment Configuration\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `NODE_ENV` | No | `development` | Environment mode (`development` or `production`) |\n| `PORT` | No | `3000` | Development server port |\n| `ALGOLIA_APP_ID` | No | - | Algolia application ID |\n| `ALGOLIA_API_KEY` | No | - | Algolia search API key |\n| `ALGOLIA_INDEX_NAME` | No | - | Algolia index name |\n\n## Regeneration\n\nIf Docusaurus version updates are needed:\n\n```bash\n# Update Docusaurus to latest version\ncd docs\nnpm update @docusaurus/core @docusaurus/preset-classic\n\n# Verify build still works\nnpm run build\n\n# Check for breaking changes in changelog\n# https://docusaurus.io/releases\n```\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Dependency Updates**: Regularly update Docusaurus and dependencies to patch security vulnerabilities\n2. **Content Security Policy**: Configure CSP headers for production deployment\n3. **XSS Prevention**: Sanitize any user-generated content in MDX components\n4. **API Key Protection**: Never commit Algolia API keys to repository; use GitHub Secrets\n\n## Performance Optimization\n\n1. **Image Optimization**: Use WebP format and lazy loading for images\n2. **Code Splitting**: Docusaurus automatically code-splits by route\n3. **Tree Shaking**: Ensure custom components are tree-shakeable\n4. **Cache Strategy**: Configure proper caching headers for static assets\n5. **Build Time**: Monitor build time; optimize if > 2 minutes\n\n## Accessibility\n\n1. **Semantic HTML**: Use proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)\n2. **Alt Text**: All images must have descriptive alt text\n3. **Keyboard Navigation**: Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard-accessible\n4. **Color Contrast**: Meet WCAG AA contrast requirements\n5. **Screen Reader Support**: Test with screen readers (NVDA, VoiceOver)\n\n## Monitoring and Analytics\n\n1. **Google Analytics**: Optional integration via Docusaurus plugin\n2. **Broken Link Monitoring**: Run link checker in CI/CD\n3. **Build Performance**: Track build times in GitHub Actions\n4. **User Feedback**: Add feedback widget (optional)\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **Blog Section**: Enable Docusaurus blog for release announcements\n2. **Versioning**: Implement full versioning for multiple releases\n3. **Interactive Examples**: Add CodeSandbox or StackBlitz embeds\n4. **API Playground**: Integrate Swagger UI for API testing\n5. **Community Translations**: Enable community-contributed translations\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/design.md","time":{"start":1775892741848,"end":1775892741863}}}}
